tasks.description:
Establish the shared contract: one `SessionSettings` type, a narrow injectable port, and a runtime-declared default permission mode. No runtime/route behavior change in this task â€” contract only.

FILE 1: `packages/shared/src/schemas.ts`. The five settings fields are currently inlined in `UpdateSessionRequestSchema` (lines 131-142). Add a reusable `SessionSettingsSchema` and refactor `UpdateSessionRequestSchema` to extend it. Insert immediately before the existing `UpdateSessionRequestSchema` declaration and replace that declaration:

```ts
export const SessionSettingsSchema = z.object({
  permissionMode: PermissionModeSchema.optional(),
  model: z.string().optional(),
  effort: EffortLevelSchema.optional(),
  fastMode: z.boolean().optional(),
  autoMode: z.boolean().optional(),
});
export type SessionSettings = z.infer<typeof SessionSettingsSchema>;

// Refactor the existing request schema to reuse it:
export const UpdateSessionRequestSchema = SessionSettingsSchema.extend({
  title: z.string().min(1).max(200).optional(),
}).openapi('UpdateSessionRequest');
```

Keep the existing `export type UpdateSessionRequest = z.infer<typeof UpdateSessionRequestSchema>;`. `PermissionModeSchema` (line 17) and `EffortLevelSchema` (line 98) already exist in this file. Preserve the `.openapi('UpdateSessionRequest')` registration so OpenAPI docs are unaffected.

FILE 2: `packages/shared/src/agent-runtime.ts`. Add the narrow port interface and the optional setter, mirroring the existing `AgentRegistryPort`/`RelayPort` + `setMeshCore`/`setRelay` pattern. Import `SessionSettings` from `./types.js` (add it to the existing type import block at the top). Add the port interface near `AgentRegistryPort`/`RelayPort` (around line 65):

```ts
/**
 * Narrow port for durable per-session settings. The API core implements this
 * (over session_metadata) and injects it into runtimes; runtimes never touch
 * the DB directly. Mirrors AgentRegistryPort/RelayPort. See ADR-0260.
 */
export interface SessionSettingsPort {
  getSessionSettings(sessionId: string): Promise<SessionSettings | null>;
  saveSessionSettings(sessionId: string, settings: SessionSettings): Promise<void>;
}
```

Add the optional setter on the `AgentRuntime` interface, in the `--- Dependency injection (optional) ---` block alongside `setMeshCore?`/`setRelay?` (around line 461-465):

```ts
/** Inject the core session-settings store for durable hydrate/write-through. */
setSessionSettings?(port: SessionSettingsPort): void;
```

Add a runtime-declared default to `RuntimeCapabilities.permissionModes` (currently lines 131-134). Change the shape to:

```ts
permissionModes: {
  supported: boolean;
  /** Mode id used when a session has no stored preference (NULL in the store). */
  default: string;
  values: PermissionModeDescriptor[];
};
```

Note: `SessionSettings` will need to be exported from `@dorkos/shared/types` â€” it is defined in `schemas.ts` and `types.ts` re-exports schema types; add the re-export there if the barrel does not pick it up automatically.

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
- `SessionSettingsSchema` exists; `UpdateSessionRequestSchema` is `SessionSettingsSchema.extend({ title })` and still has all original fields (permissionMode, model, effort, fastMode, autoMode, title) and the OpenAPI registration.
- `SessionSettingsPort` and `AgentRuntime.setSessionSettings?` exist; the setter is optional.
- `RuntimeCapabilities.permissionModes` has a required `default: string` field.
- `pnpm typecheck` passes for `@dorkos/shared` (this task intentionally breaks the two capability constants that omit `default` â€” those are fixed in task 2.2).
VERIFY: `pnpm --filter @dorkos/shared typecheck` (expect only the two missing-`default` errors in the server's runtime-constants, addressed by 2.2).

Make `RuntimeRegistry` the authoritative owner of session-settings persistence by implementing the `SessionSettingsPort` structurally (it already owns `session_metadata` and the DB handle and can satisfy the `runtime NOT NULL` constraint via `getSessionRuntimeType`).

FILE: `apps/server/src/services/core/runtime-registry.ts`. Add three methods to the `RuntimeRegistry` class. Import `SessionSettings` from `@dorkos/shared/types` (or `@dorkos/shared/agent-runtime`) at the top. Implement:

```ts
async getSessionSettings(sessionId: string): Promise<SessionSettings | null> {
  const db = this.requireDb('getSessionSettings');
  const row = db
    .select({
      permissionMode: sessionMetadata.permissionMode,
      model: sessionMetadata.model,
      effort: sessionMetadata.effort,
      fastMode: sessionMetadata.fastMode,
      autoMode: sessionMetadata.autoMode,
    })
    .from(sessionMetadata)
    .where(eq(sessionMetadata.sessionId, sessionId))
    .get();
  if (!row) return null;
  // NULL column -> omitted key (do not surface explicit nulls as values).
  const settings: SessionSettings = {};
  if (row.permissionMode != null) settings.permissionMode = row.permissionMode as SessionSettings['permissionMode'];
  if (row.model != null) settings.model = row.model;
  if (row.effort != null) settings.effort = row.effort as SessionSettings['effort'];
  if (row.fastMode != null) settings.fastMode = row.fastMode;
  if (row.autoMode != null) settings.autoMode = row.autoMode;
  return settings;
}

async saveSessionSettings(sessionId: string, settings: SessionSettings): Promise<void> {
  const db = this.requireDb('saveSessionSettings');
  // only keys explicitly provided are written
  const patch: Partial<typeof sessionMetadata.$inferInsert> = {};
  if (settings.permissionMode !== undefined) patch.permissionMode = settings.permissionMode;
  if (settings.model !== undefined) patch.model = settings.model;
  if (settings.effort !== undefined) patch.effort = settings.effort;
  if (settings.fastMode !== undefined) patch.fastMode = settings.fastMode;
  if (settings.autoMode !== undefined) patch.autoMode = settings.autoMode;
  if (Object.keys(patch).length === 0) return;
  const runtime = await this.getSessionRuntimeType(sessionId); // infer 'claude-code' if no row
  db.insert(sessionMetadata)
    .values({ sessionId, runtime, createdAt: new Date().toISOString(), ...patch })
    .onConflictDoUpdate({ target: sessionMetadata.sessionId, set: patch }) // identity columns untouched on conflict
    .run();
}

/** Batch read for the list-route overlay (not part of the narrow port). */
getSessionSettingsMany(ids: string[]): Map<string, SessionSettings> { /* single `WHERE sessionId IN (...)` */ }
```

Implement `getSessionSettingsMany` with a single `db.select(...).from(sessionMetadata).where(inArray(sessionMetadata.sessionId, ids)).all()` query (import `inArray` from `@dorkos/db` / `drizzle-orm`; add it to the re-export in `packages/db/src/index.ts` line 54 if not already exported), mapping each row to a `SessionSettings` with the same NULL-to-omitted logic as `getSessionSettings`. Return an empty `Map` when `ids` is empty (skip the query). Add full TSDoc to all three methods.

UPSERT semantics to preserve: creates the row (with inferred runtime) if a PATCH arrives before the first message; otherwise updates only the provided setting columns, leaving identity (`runtime`, `agentPath`, `createdAt`) intact via `onConflictDoUpdate({ set: patch })`.

TESTS: `apps/server/src/services/core/__tests__/runtime-registry.test.ts` (extend the existing file or create it). Use a real in-memory better-sqlite3 DB via `createDb(':memory:')` + `runMigrations(db)` from `@dorkos/db`, then `registry.setDb(db)`. Cases:
- `saveSessionSettings` UPSERT creates a row with the inferred runtime (`'claude-code'`) when none exists.
- `saveSessionSettings` on an existing row updates only the provided columns and leaves `runtime`/`agentPath`/`createdAt` intact on conflict (seed a row via `persistSessionRuntime` first, then patch only `permissionMode`).
- `saveSessionSettings` with an empty/all-undefined settings object is a no-op (no row created).
- `getSessionSettings` maps `NULL` columns to omitted keys (a row with only `permissionMode` set returns `{ permissionMode }` with no `model`/`effort` keys).
- Booleans round-trip correctly (`fastMode: true`, `autoMode: false` persist and read back as booleans, not 1/0).
- `getSessionSettingsMany` batch-reads multiple ids in one call and returns a `Map`; empty input returns an empty `Map`.

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: all unit tests pass; methods satisfy `SessionSettingsPort` structurally.
VERIFY: `pnpm vitest run apps/server/src/services/core/__tests__/runtime-registry.test.ts` and `pnpm typecheck`.

Make the claude-code runtime a pure executor that hydrates from and writes through to the core store, and wire the port at the composition root. Also fix the two capability constants to declare a `default`.

FILE 1: `packages/shared/src/agent-runtime.ts` â€” widen `SessionOpts` and `MessageOpts` to carry all five settings. `SessionOpts` (currently lines 143-148) becomes the settings plus cwd/hasStarted:

```ts
export interface SessionOpts extends SessionSettings {
  permissionMode: PermissionMode; // required here (final fallback already resolved)
  cwd?: string;
  hasStarted?: boolean;
}
```

Note `SessionSettings.permissionMode` is optional but `SessionOpts.permissionMode` must stay required (the caller resolves the fallback before calling). Add `model?`, `effort?`, `fastMode?`, `autoMode?` to `MessageOpts` (currently lines 150-163) by extending `SessionSettings` (keep the existing `cwd`, `systemPromptAppend`, `uiState`, `title` fields and their TSDoc).

FILE 2: `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/sessions/session-store.ts`. Add the injected port + default mode and a `configureSettings` method to the `SessionStore` class:

```ts
private settingsPort?: SessionSettingsPort;
private defaultPermissionMode: PermissionMode = 'default';
/** Inject the core settings store and the runtime's default fallback mode. */
configureSettings(port: SessionSettingsPort, defaultMode: PermissionMode): void {
  this.settingsPort = port;
  this.defaultPermissionMode = defaultMode;
}
```

Import `SessionSettingsPort` from `@dorkos/shared/agent-runtime`. In `ensureForMessage` (lines 86-119), in the cold path (`if (!existing)`), read persisted settings once and seed with precedence `per-send override (opts) -> persisted -> runtime default`. Replace the current `this.ensureSession(sessionId, { permissionMode: opts?.permissionMode ?? 'default', cwd: opts?.cwd, hasStarted: hasTranscript })` block with:

```ts
const persisted = await this.settingsPort?.getSessionSettings(sessionId);
this.ensureSession(sessionId, {
  permissionMode: opts?.permissionMode ?? persisted?.permissionMode ?? this.defaultPermissionMode,
  model: opts?.model ?? persisted?.model,
  effort: opts?.effort ?? persisted?.effort,
  fastMode: opts?.fastMode ?? persisted?.fastMode,
  autoMode: opts?.autoMode ?? persisted?.autoMode,
  cwd: opts?.cwd,
  hasStarted: hasTranscript,
});
```

In `ensureSession` (lines 53-78), seed all five settings on the in-memory `AgentSession` (currently only `permissionMode`/`cwd`/`hasStarted` are set). Add to the `this.sessions.set(...)` object: `model: opts.model, effort: opts.effort, fastMode: opts.fastMode, autoMode: opts.autoMode` (the `AgentSession` type in `agent-types.ts` already has these optional fields).

WRITE-THROUGH in `updateSession` (lines 155-201): persist the user's choice FIRST so intent is durable regardless of the live query. At the top of the method (after resolving/auto-creating the session), build a `changedSettings` object from the provided opts (only defined keys) and `await this.settingsPort?.saveSessionSettings(sessionId, changedSettings)` before mutating in-memory state. (The best-effort live-apply / no-revert change to the `setPermissionMode` block is task 2.3 â€” do NOT change the revert behavior here; 2.3 owns that.) Only user-driven PATCHes reach `updateSession`, so transient per-send overrides are never persisted.

FILE 3: `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/claude-code-runtime.ts`. Add a `setSessionSettings` method forwarding to the store, placed in the dependency-injection block alongside `setMeshCore` (around line 119-122):

```ts
/** Inject the core session-settings store for durable hydrate/write-through. */
setSessionSettings(port: SessionSettingsPort): void {
  this.sessionStore.configureSettings(port, CLAUDE_CODE_CAPABILITIES.permissionModes.default);
}
```

Import `SessionSettingsPort` from `@dorkos/shared/agent-runtime`. `CLAUDE_CODE_CAPABILITIES` is already imported (line 33).

FILE 4: `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/runtime-constants.ts`. Add `default: 'default',` to `CLAUDE_CODE_CAPABILITIES.permissionModes` (insert between `supported: true,` on line 30 and `values: [` on line 31).

FILE 5: `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/test-mode/runtime-constants.ts`. Add a `default` to `TEST_MODE_CAPABILITIES.permissionModes` (around line 36-37). Use `default: 'always-allow',` (the first declared test-mode mode id; test-mode ids deliberately differ from Claude's).

FILE 6: `apps/server/src/index.ts`. Wire the port at the composition root. `runtimeRegistry.setDb(db)` is at line 131; `claudeRuntime` is registered at line 191; `claudeRuntime.setMeshCore(meshCore)` is at line 279. Add, after `setDb` has run and `claudeRuntime` is non-null (alongside the `if (claudeRuntime) { claudeRuntime.setMeshCore(meshCore); ... }` block near line 278):

```ts
claudeRuntime.setSessionSettings(runtimeRegistry); // registry satisfies SessionSettingsPort structurally
```

`TestModeRuntime` leaves the optional `setSessionSettings` setter unimplemented (no behavior change) â€” do not add it there.

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
- Cold `ensureForMessage` with a persisted row hydrates all five settings with precedence opts > persisted > runtime default.
- `ensureSession` seeds all five settings on the in-memory session.
- `updateSession` calls `saveSessionSettings` with exactly the changed fields, persisting before in-memory mutation.
- Both capability constants compile with the new required `default` field; the test-mode `default` is a valid test-mode mode id.
- `pnpm typecheck`, `pnpm lint`, and the existing claude-code/session-store/test-mode capabilities tests pass.
VERIFY: `pnpm typecheck && pnpm lint && pnpm vitest run apps/server/src/services/runtimes/test-mode/__tests__/capabilities.test.ts`.

Allow instant permission-mode switching on active sessions (including escalation to bypass) with no 422/revert, by always launching SDK queries with the bypass capability and making the live `setPermissionMode` best-effort.

FILE 1: `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/messaging/message-sender.ts`. The current block at lines 235-238 reads:

```ts
sdkOptions.permissionMode = session.permissionMode;
if (session.permissionMode === 'bypassPermissions') {
  sdkOptions.allowDangerouslySkipPermissions = true;
}
```

Replace it so the flag is set UNCONDITIONALLY, decoupled from the current mode (remove the `if` guard):

```ts
// Was: only when session.permissionMode === 'bypassPermissions'
sdkOptions.permissionMode = session.permissionMode;
sdkOptions.allowDangerouslySkipPermissions = true; // always â€” grants the capability to switch live
```

Why this is safe (empirically verified, ADR-0261): an isolated SDK probe ran `query()` in `default` mode with and without the flag; both invoked `canUseTool` for `Write` and honored a `deny` (file not written) â€” identical behavior. The flag is a pure capability gate the SDK consults only when `permissionMode === 'bypassPermissions'`; it does not weaken `default`/`acceptEdits`/`plan`/`dontAsk` (documented evaluation order: Hooks -> Deny -> Permission mode -> Allow -> `canUseTool`). The single tool-executing launch point is the `query(...)` call at `message-sender.ts:290`. The warm-up `query()` in `runtime-cache.ts:184` (`query({ prompt: neverYield, options: { cwd } })`) never executes tools and is unaffected â€” leave it alone.

FILE 2: `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/sessions/session-store.ts`. Make `updateSession`'s live mode switch best-effort. The current block (lines 176-195) reverts and re-throws on failure:

```ts
if (opts.permissionMode) {
  const prevMode = session.permissionMode;
  session.permissionMode = opts.permissionMode;
  if (session.activeQuery) {
    try {
      await session.activeQuery.setPermissionMode(
        opts.permissionMode as Parameters<typeof session.activeQuery.setPermissionMode>[0]
      );
    } catch (err) {
      session.permissionMode = prevMode;
      logger.error('[updateSession] setPermissionMode failed', { sessionId, err });
      throw err;
    }
  }
  ...
}
```

Change it so the persisted/in-memory mode is kept on live-apply failure â€” do NOT revert (`session.permissionMode = prevMode`) and do NOT re-throw. On a failed live `setPermissionMode`, log it and keep the new mode (it applies on the next turn). With the flag now always present (FILE 1), the bypass switch succeeds instantly mid-run. The write-through `saveSessionSettings` (added in task 2.2) already persisted intent first, so the order is: persist -> set in-memory mode -> best-effort live apply.

FILE 3: `apps/server/src/routes/sessions.ts`. The PATCH handler (lines 132-159) wraps `runtime.updateSession(...)` in a try/catch that returns `sendError(res, 422, ..., 'PERMISSION_MODE_FAILED')`. Since `updateSession` no longer throws on live-apply failure, this 422 path becomes dead. Remove the 422 try/catch around `runtime.updateSession` and call it directly (keep the `if (!updated) return sendError(res, 404, ...)` check). Do not introduce any new error code for live-apply failures â€” the contract is now no-422/no-revert.

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
- `message-sender.ts` sets `sdkOptions.allowDangerouslySkipPermissions = true` unconditionally; the `if (session.permissionMode === 'bypassPermissions')` guard is gone.
- `session-store.ts` `updateSession` no longer has the `prevMode` revert and no longer re-throws on live-apply failure; the failure is swallowed (logged) and the new mode is retained.
- `sessions.ts` PATCH no longer returns 422 for a failed live mode switch.
- The warm-up query in `runtime-cache.ts:184` is untouched.
- `pnpm typecheck` and `pnpm lint` pass; existing message-sender / session-store tests pass (update any test that asserted the old 422/revert behavior).
VERIFY: `pnpm typecheck && pnpm lint && pnpm vitest run apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/__tests__/`.

Unify the three display surfaces (session-list badge, in-session toolbar, enforcement) by overlaying the persisted store over transcript-derived values in the HTTP read routes. Display overlay lives in the route (HTTP-only) so the narrow port is not widened with batch-read methods; the route already imports `runtimeRegistry`.

FILE: `apps/server/src/routes/sessions.ts`.

GET /:id (lines 53-67): after `const session = await runtime.getSession(projectDir, internalSessionId);` and the `if (!session) return 404` check, overlay persisted settings. Read `const stored = await runtimeRegistry.getSessionSettings(internalSessionId);` and, when `stored` is non-null, assign each defined stored field onto `session` (store wins; transcript = fallback for legacy rows). For example:

```ts
const stored = await runtimeRegistry.getSessionSettings(internalSessionId);
if (stored) {
  if (stored.permissionMode !== undefined) session.permissionMode = stored.permissionMode;
  if (stored.model !== undefined) session.model = stored.model;
  if (stored.effort !== undefined) session.effort = stored.effort;
  if (stored.fastMode !== undefined) session.fastMode = stored.fastMode;
  if (stored.autoMode !== undefined) session.autoMode = stored.autoMode;
}
res.json(session);
```

GET / (list, lines 25-40): after `const sessions = await runtime.listSessions(projectDir);`, batch-read with one query and overlay per session (no N+1). Use the session ids from the listed sessions:

```ts
const storedMany = runtimeRegistry.getSessionSettingsMany(sessions.map((s) => s.id));
for (const s of sessions) {
  const stored = storedMany.get(s.id);
  if (!stored) continue;
  if (stored.permissionMode !== undefined) s.permissionMode = stored.permissionMode;
  if (stored.model !== undefined) s.model = stored.model;
  if (stored.effort !== undefined) s.effort = stored.effort;
  if (stored.fastMode !== undefined) s.fastMode = stored.fastMode;
  if (stored.autoMode !== undefined) s.autoMode = stored.autoMode;
}
res.json(sessions.slice(0, limit));
```

Note `getSessionSettingsMany` is synchronous (returns a `Map`, no `await`); `getSessionSettings` is async. Consider extracting the per-session field overlay into a small local helper to avoid duplicating the five assignments (DRY / 3-strike rule). A legacy session with no stored row must fall back to the transcript-derived values without error (the overlay is skipped when `stored` is null/missing).

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
- `GET /:id` returns stored values over transcript-derived ones; legacy sessions (no row) fall back to transcript without error.
- `GET /` overlays stored values via a single batch query (no per-session DB call).
- After this, badge (list), toolbar (`getSession`), and enforcement read the same persisted values.
- `pnpm typecheck` and `pnpm lint` pass.
VERIFY: `pnpm typecheck && pnpm lint && pnpm vitest run apps/server/src/routes/__tests__/sessions.test.ts` (if present).
